# Anyo
Assessment details:
Instructions:
 You are expected to write clean, efficient, and well-documented code.
 You can use any programming language or framework of your choice.
Task 1: Write code to solve the problem: Implement a RESTful API for a simple application 
that allows users to create, read, update, and delete users. Use any programming language 
and framework of your choice.
Requirements:
 Endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting users.
 Proper error handling and status codes for different scenarios.
 Persistence of user data using a database.
You will be assessed on the following criteria:
 Correctness of the solution.
 Code quality, including readability and maintainability.
 Proper use of RESTful principles.
 Effective error handling.
Task 2: Data Processing
Create a CSV file (data.csv) containing the following fields: id, name, age, email, phone, and 
address. Write a script or function that reads the CSV file, processes the data, and performs 
the following tasks:
 Calculate the average age of all individuals in the file.
 Filter out individuals who are under 18 years old.
 Sort the remaining individuals by name in ascending order.
 Save the filtered and sorted data into a new CSV file (output.csv) with the same 
fields.
Requirements:
 Use any library or tool of your choice to handle CSV file operations.
 Write clean and maintainable code with proper error handling.
 Include documentation or comments to explain your approach.
